97.name: PetM family cytochrome b6-f complex subunit 7
all_names: PetM family cytochrome b6-f complex subunit 7
PetM family cytochrome b6-f complex subunit 7
PetM family cytochrome b6-f complex subunit 7

function.Function_description: Component of the cytochrome b6-f complex, which mediates electron transfer between photosystem II (PSII) and photosystem I (PSI), cyclic electron flow around PSI, and state transitions

Catalyzes the NAD(P)-dependent oxidation of 4-(phosphooxy)-L-threonine (HTP) into 2-amino-3-oxo-4-(phosphooxy)butyric acid which spontaneously decarboxylates to form 3-amino-2-oxopropyl phosphate (AHAP)

99.name: signal recognition particle protein
all_names: Signal Recognition Particle (SRP) component with 4.5S RNA (ffs)

GO_terms: P:SRP-dependent cotranslational protein targeting to membrane
function.Function_description: Involved in targeting and insertion of nascent membrane proteins into the cytoplasmic membrane. Binds to the hydrophobic signal sequence of the ribosome-nascent chain (RNC) as it emerges from the ribosomes. The SRP-RNC complex is then targeted to the cytoplasmic membrane where it interacts with the SRP receptor FtsY

An essential GTPase that binds both GDP and GTP, with rapid nucleotide exchange. Plays a role in 16S rRNA processing and 30S ribosomal subunit biogenesis and possibly also in cell cycle regulation and energy metabolism

GO_terms: P:isopentenyl diphosphate biosynthetic process, methylerythritol 4-phosphate pathway
function.Function_description: Catalyzes the conversion of 1-hydroxy-2-methyl-2-(E)-butenyl 4-diphosphate (HMBPP) into a mixture of isopentenyl diphosphate (IPP) and dimethylallyl diphosphate (DMAPP). Acts in the terminal step of the DOXP/MEP pathway for isoprenoid precursor biosynthesis
